gpgme
-------------------------------------------
GPGME  (GnuPG Made Easy) is a C language library that allows to add 
support for cryptography to a program. It is designed to make access to 
public key crypto engines like GnuPG easier for applications. 
GPGME provides a high-level crypto API for encryption, decryption, 
signing, signature verification and key management.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-1.5.19-4
  gnupg-1.4.2.1-1
  libgpg-error-1.1-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  cygwin-1.5.19-4
  autoconf2.5-2.59-3
  automake1.9-1.9.6-1
  binutils-20050610-1
  gawk-3.1.5-2
  gcc-core-3.4.4-1
  libtool1.5-1.5.20-2
  make-3.80-1
  sed-4.1.3-1

Canonical homepage:
  http://www.gnupg.org/(en)/related_software/gpgme/

Canonical download:
  ftp://ftp.gnupg.org/gcrypt/gpgme/

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  unpack gpgme-1.0.3-1-src.tar.bz2
    if you use setup to install this src package, it will be
	 unpacked under /usr/src automatically
  cd /usr/src
  ./gpgme-1.0.3-1.sh all

This will create:
  /usr/src/gpgme-1.0.3-1-src.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/gpgme-1.0.3-1.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/libgpgme11-1.0.3-1.tar.bz2

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

  /etc/postinstall/gpgme.sh
  /usr/bin/gpgme-config
  /usr/include/gpgme-1.0/gpgme.h
  /usr/lib/libgpgme-pthread.dll.a
  /usr/lib/libgpgme-pthread.la
  /usr/lib/libgpgme.dll.a
  /usr/lib/libgpgme.la
  /usr/share/aclocal/gpgme.m4
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/gpgme-1.0.3.README
  /usr/share/doc/gpgme-1.0.3/AUTHORS
  /usr/share/doc/gpgme-1.0.3/ChangeLog
  /usr/share/doc/gpgme-1.0.3/COPYING
  /usr/share/doc/gpgme-1.0.3/INSTALL
  /usr/share/doc/gpgme-1.0.3/NEWS
  /usr/share/doc/gpgme-1.0.3/README
  /usr/share/doc/gpgme-1.0.3/THANKS
  /usr/share/doc/gpgme-1.0.3/TODO
  /usr/share/info/gpgme.info.gz

Files included in the library package:

  /usr/bin/cyggpgme-11.dll
  /usr/bin/cyggpgme-pthread-11.dll

